Rating: 3
My husband found this recipe and insisted we try it. He knew I'd approve because it had some "green" along with all egg and bacon, LOL. It was very easy to assemble and the presentation was gorgeous. I felt the spinach alone would be too bland so I put some onions in with the spinach saute and it was perfect! I also put some crumbled goat cheese on top of the muffin (and I didn't pre toast it) and a bit more on top of the egg. It added a nice creamy texture. I was craving a sauce or drizzle....since the entire thing came off as a hot spinach salad. I'm thinking next time I make it (and I most certainly will) I'll add a nice balsamic reduction and pull the whole "salad" taste together!

