Rating: 4
Wow! This was delicious and looks so fancy. Here are the changes I made to make this dish a bit more healthy and more substantial for the big eaters in my family. First, I used bigger 2 cup ramekins. Then I placed two toasted english muffin halves in the bottom of each (one cut in half to fit the bottom of the ramekin better). Instead of bacon I used smoked ham lunch meat (three pieces per ramekin, browned in the skillet and placed on top of the bread). Topped this with the spinach and then two to three cracked eggs. Next, I substituted chunky tomato pasta sauce instead of cream. I also sprinkled a little shredded Italian style cheese on top as suggested by another reviewer. Then I baked at 425 degrees for 10 minutes. Perfect! The eggs were just done, a little runny, but the whites were done. The tomato sauce was flavorful and added color to the dish. I can't wait to make this for guests.

