Rating: 4
What's not to like? If you like spinach/eggs/bacon, that is. In my childhood, Mom would open and heat a can or two of spinach, and serve it up with sliced boiled egg and fried bacon and buttered toast on the side. For the last 40 years, my husband and I have enjoyed the same for a quick lite supper or Saturday lunch. We've also baked eggs with cream or sour cream and frequently added ham or bacon. This updates two old favorite standbys beautifully. YUMM!!